ษออออออออออออออออออออป
บ Game Configuration บ
ศออออออออออออออออออออผ
    To configure World Quest, run the wqsetup.exe program. Choose your
language by pressing either F1 or F2.  The setup program will display
a menu of choices about your system hardware and game options.
Use the arrow keys to move the cursor, and the enter key selects an option.
When changing the game and opening delays, press the up or down arrow
key to change the value.    

The data directory should be set to the current directory unless you are
running World Quest from a CD-ROM.  If this is the case, then set the
data directory to a drive where your configuration files and high scores
may be written.   Once you have saved your configuration in a data directory,
you should always run World Quest and the setup program from the WQ2DATA 
directory by running the following batch files:
wqsetup.bat - Runs the setup program
wqe.bat     - Runs World Quest (English version)
wqd.bat     - Runs World Quest (German version)

If you do not run the programs from this directory, they will not be able
to find your configuration for the game.



ษอออออออออออป
บ Main Menu บ
ศอออออออออออผ
The menu looks like this:

   Play Game
Enter Level Code
  Instructions
  Ordering Info
    Credits
  High Scores
   Quit Game

Use the arrow keys (or joystick) to select an option, and hit return
(or press joystick button) to execute the option.

High scores are viewed only from the main menu. To reset the high score
table, delete the file high.sco.


After reading the info on the main menu, select start game to begin
your quest. You must venture around the surface of several planets,
in order to destroy the aliens populating the area. Once you've
secured the planet, your race can begin rebuilding its own cities.


